Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.09,0:02:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,First question.\NHe's a graduate student, and he's studying neurofeedback,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.30,0:02:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wants to know what does it calibrate at.\NNeurofeedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Neurofeedback.\NNeurofeedback with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.81,0:02:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Please explain.\NNeurofeedback with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.25,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What is neurofeedback?\NOkay, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.31,0:02:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask about this, yes.\NWe can calibrate the neurofeedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:03:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 440, 460, 450.\N450 is my guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.83,0:03:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, 450.\N450.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.46,0:03:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After you do this many, many times,\Nyou begin to almost intuit what the number is going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.22,0:03:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You get like a feeling for it, you know.\NSo 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.65,0:03:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's science.\NScience is in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.74,0:03:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Newtonian paradigm of reality.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.11,0:03:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll read this question in Korean so other Koreans can understand.\NOh, yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.81,0:03:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus died on the cross to redeem all human sins,\Nas the Church says.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:04:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's true,\Ndid all of you here, including me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.31,0:04:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,suffer the same sin?\NWe are told in Korean,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.83,0:04:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Christian theology,\Nthat the meaning of Jesus Christ's crucifixion on the cross,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of that was to redeem ourselves from our sin.\NIs that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.35,0:04:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that is so,\Nthrough that sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.08,0:04:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ's sacrifice,\Nare we all redeemed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who believe on his name are redeemed by his sacrifice.\NNow, he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.25,0:04:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,incarnate, incarnate.\NThose who believe on Jesus Christ are redeemed by Jesus Christ's sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.89,0:05:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Incarnate means that his divinity was a direct gift from God.\NJesus Christ was incarnate as a direct gift from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo, Jesus Christ's divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.64,0:05:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was like a spark,\NYes. So, Jesus Christ's divinity was like a spark,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.61,0:05:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a special recognition from God,\Nthat Jesus would serve a certain purpose for mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.16,0:05:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to redeem mankind.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.22,0:05:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ's incarnation,\Nwas a direct gift from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.22,0:05:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nit was a gift from God to save mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.56,0:06:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So,\Nthe biblical story is that man fell from grace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God's laws.\NAnd by Jesus Christ's sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,man redeemed himself,\Nbecame redeemed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.94,0:06:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that all who believe on his name,\Nor acknowledge his divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,are thereby also redeemed.\NSo, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.37,0:06:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible,\Nit says that man fell from grace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.69,0:06:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God's laws.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.69,0:06:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's a historical fact,\Nthat man fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.69,0:06:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a biblical,\Nin the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.69,0:06:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it says,\Nman fell from innocence and grace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.04,0:06:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God.\NIt's in the Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.24,0:06:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's in the Scripture.\NIt's in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.24,0:07:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It says,\Nman fell from innocence and grace
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God.\NThat's in the Scripture, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.87,0:07:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And by Christ's sacrifice,\Nhe redeemed mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those who believe in Christ,\NJesus is their advocate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.95,0:07:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,advocate before the Father.\NJesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I will,\NI will plead for you before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.00,0:08:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,\NI will plead for you before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.70,0:08:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,\NI will plead for you before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.02,0:08:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,\Nwhen you are the 1st,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you are the 2nd.\NThat's the promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.50,0:08:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The promise is true.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.50,0:08:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he only asked about Jesus.\NAnd when we calibrate the level of Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.81,0:08:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we get 1000,\Nwhich is the maximum possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If we measure Jesus,\NSo those who believe in Krishna, then Krishna says those who believe in me belong to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.40,0:09:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha says you're on your own.\NBuddha says you're on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the meaning of yuna is that if you were a little bit foolish in this life, then you can do well in the next life.\NMy question is about on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.07,0:10:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you're on your own every moment, but it doesn't feel like you've grown up in a Buddhist family.\NCan you say that by realizing the pain that occurs every moment, you're letting go of that pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.91,0:10:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that we need to surrender to God every instant.\NAnd I grew up in Buddhist family and this teaching doesn't jive well with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then can I understand that dedication as meaning that when every feeling of pain,\Nwhen every feeling of pain as they arises, I should, by recognizing it, I surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.80,0:11:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the same? Am I understanding it correctly?\NYou surrender everything to God all the time, including feelings and occurrences and thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.79,0:11:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NYou surrender everything to God continuously as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I clearly being aware of it? Is that the act of surrendering?\NI have to think back years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As a thing arises, you surrender it to God.\NYou let go wanting to control it or change it or make it different or squeeze it for some profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.84,0:11:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is as it is.\NWhatever happens, whatever it is, surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.47,0:12:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to gain any profit from it.\NSurrender everything to God voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Dr. Hopkins' experience in the past.\NThat is sort of like a practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.55,0:12:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, there's nothing to surrender to God.\NEverything just is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.55,0:12:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the birds flying along.\NAnd you let the bird be. You let all of life be like the bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.65,0:12:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice interpreter.\NNice table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.65,0:12:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful wife.\NNice water.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.65,0:12:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good soda.\NNice Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.65,0:13:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything just is as it is.\NIt doesn't involve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena are all occurring of their own.\NAll is occurring of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.03,0:13:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of its own nature.\NBecause all that seems to be occurring is only an observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.55,0:13:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And creation is continuous.\NCreation is constantly unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you witness the unfolding of creation.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.10,0:13:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.10,0:13:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:14:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NSo you don't have to get involved in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If it rains, it rains, if it shines, it shines.\NIt's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.10,0:14:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice rainy day.\NIt's a nice sunny day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.28,0:14:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice warm day.\NOh, it's a nice cool day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.28,0:14:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good day. It's a good day because it's cool.\NIt's all okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.80,0:14:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is okay.\NThat happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happens of its own.\NEverything happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.08,0:14:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, you release it, you release it, you release it.\NAnd then after that, it lets go of its own because you don't get attached, so you don't have to let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.10,0:14:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're not attached, you don't have to let it go.\NYou consciously let go of it, but if you keep doing it, you just don't have any obsession with it, so you naturally accept everything as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.34,0:15:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But for me, when I hear the word God, I don't have any special image at all.\NWhen he thinks of God, he cannot conceptualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.86,0:15:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No image appears.\NRight, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.55,0:15:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And to what is surrendering?\NWhat you're looking at, what you're looking at is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.66,0:15:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God.\NThis is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God.\NEverything is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is the expression of divinity.\NYou see the sacredness of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.30,0:15:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all that exists.\NThe sacredness of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.59,0:16:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of this table.\NThis is God's expression as a table.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.09,0:16:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,God's expression is Kleenex.\NGod's expression is water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is divinity.\NIt's an expression of the sacredness as a table, and the sacredness as a Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.08,0:16:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is the sacredness.\NWith an enlightened state, the divinity of everything shines forth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.44,0:16:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with complete beauty and holiness.\NBeauty and perfection, everything is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.89,0:17:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you have to do or fix, and with that realization, you see the beauty\Nof all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the beauty of all that exists, beauty.\NCharm, the charm of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.86,0:17:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NNext question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one with hearing disability.\NAnd he has a hearing disability.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,His question is, he's asking you to pray for his mother, who died of cancer.\NI think I understand quite recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.08,0:17:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you pray for his mother, deceased mother?\NWhy should I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.75,0:18:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NGod doesn't like her, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.64,0:18:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He just wanted to get more of a blessing, actually.\NOh, oh, oh, oh, I see, oh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anyone have sign language?\NDid she have a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she have a name?\NWho did you pray for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.69,0:18:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you pray for your mother?\NWhat's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother?\NName, name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Kim Gyeong Nam.\NKim Gyeong Nam.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.17,0:18:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMother's soul is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.78,0:18:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother's soul is okay.\NHe says his mother's soul is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.81,0:18:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to worry.\NHe says you don't have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.90,0:19:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is, would a writer's way be fit for my job?\NIf it's suitable, a documentary or a simple literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.61,0:19:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh.\NShe's asking whether becoming a professional writer is appropriate for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.57,0:19:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, she works for a TV station as a writer.\NAnd then she's asking whether that job, that vocation is good for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.70,0:19:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, for documentary or for pure literature.\NMundane question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.22,0:19:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the question?\NShe wants to be a good writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.82,0:19:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Good writer.\NGood writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.73,0:20:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And also she's asking for your advice to be a good writer.\NTo be a good writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.07,0:20:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's see.\NWe have permission to ask about this lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.57,0:20:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She has the talent to be a good writer.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.90,0:20:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, writing, you become energized by what they call the muse.\NM-U-S-E in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.75,0:20:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Muse.\NThe muse is like inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.53,0:20:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspiration.\NSo, when my muse is present, I feel energized and interested in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I get up at 3.\NOr 4 o'clock in the morning and start to write, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.49,0:20:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I get up 3 or 4 o'clock.\NI have to jump out of bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.23,0:21:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to write.\NTo be a good writer, you need inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.44,0:21:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We usually say that inspiration is what we feel.\NYou need inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.96,0:21:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In the case of Dr. Hawkins, if you have that inspiration, you can wake up at 3 o'clock in the morning and write.\NSo, for some years, I wrote books.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.20,0:21:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the muse.\Nwas initiating the desire to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.90,0:21:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But now my views is quiet, thank goodness.\NI wrote eight or nine books, nine stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.55,0:22:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight books, or nine books, I don't know what.\NAnd then, now maybe I'm thinking about writing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.25,0:22:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,another little book, commentaries, thoughts\Nand commentaries about things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.03,0:22:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But not a big book like before, you know.\NSo, follow your muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.13,0:22:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't, don't try and make yourself right\Nwhen you don't feel the incentive, the energy, the desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.42,0:22:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that in Korean?\NMuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.44,0:22:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Muuu sse.\NIs that a familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually we say feel.\NYou get a feel first up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.94,0:23:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NWell, in English it's almost like, almost like a fantasy that you're muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.28,0:23:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I must write.\NI must dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.28,0:23:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I must sing.\NI must be an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.76,0:23:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspires you.\NInspires you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.41,0:23:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.\NHe's a student who is studying psychoanalysis?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.27,0:23:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychology.\NPsychology. And then his question is, what is the meaning that dreams can provide?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.50,0:23:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dream?\NYeah. Provide to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.50,0:24:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we can analyze dreams and apply their values to our life, what are the methods of doing that?\NOh, dreams are very important in psychoanalysis. Psychoanalysis, either Freudian, Jungian, there are others too,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.88,0:24:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but Freud and Jung are the two main types of interpretations.\NAnd a great deal is learned from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.86,0:24:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because without psychoanalysis, a person is not familiar with their unconscious.\NAnd in psychoanalysis, the unconscious becomes more into awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.65,0:25:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very, very useful. And it's very, very true.\NDreams are very important in psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.75,0:25:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to understand that.\NFreud and Jung are the two main scholars.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.75,0:25:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can learn a lot from the unconscious in psychology,\Nbut through psychoanalysis, we can learn a lot from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.75,0:25:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we learn from that is very accurate.\NHe says it's close to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.75,0:25:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in psychoanalysis for, I don't know, five, six years, a long time.\NEvery day of the week, you go and lay on the couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.05,0:25:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And talk about what goes through your mind.\NAnd all the things that are repressed out of awareness now come up in awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.56,0:26:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My psychoanalysis was Freud.\NMy psychoanalyst was Professor at Columbia University.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.10,0:26:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,His psychoanalyst was psychoanalyzed by Freud.\NSo Freud is like my psychoanalytic grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.13,0:26:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So Freud is like my psychoanalytic grandfather.\NSo Freud is like my psychoanalytic grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.42,0:26:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Hawkins, you went to bed at least once a week before a certain period of time,\Nand after you lay on the couch, you raised your consciousness to the level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.42,0:26:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you raised your consciousness to the level of consciousness,\Nand the person who did that for Professor Hawkins was a professor at Columbia University,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.42,0:26:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the professor who taught him was Freud.\NAnd I wanted to talk about Freud to Professor Hawkins
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.42,0:27:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was the grand-grandfather of the psychological analysis.\NAlso, through psychoanalysis you understand the things that go on in the world to a greater degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.85,0:27:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,With database analysis we begin to understand the things that are going on in the world to a greater degree.\NFreud said that in the unconscious, there is eros and also thanatos.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.56,0:28:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the attraction to life and the other is the attraction to death.\NThese two things he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.35,0:28:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see every day in the news somewhere there is a riot with people killing other people.\NEvery day.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.11,0:28:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day.\NWhere is it this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.85,0:28:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They are killing some, oh, today it's Greece.\NEvery day they're killing somebody someplace, and the people can't wait for the killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.24,0:28:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,People rush to the killing.\NThey just can't wait to get shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.35,0:28:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Rush to your death, attracted to the death.\NThere's a death instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.18,0:28:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it, I first saw it in a dog pack.\NI had my chickens out in the yard with the fence around, and three dogs came into the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.76,0:29:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,yard and they began attacking the chickens.\NThey would kill this chicken, then they would kill this chicken, then they would kill this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.72,0:29:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,chicken.\NThey just were on a killing bloodlust to kill, kill, kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.72,0:29:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.31,0:29:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.72,0:29:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.72,0:30:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.22,0:30:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And in today's world, like, Islamics blow up a whole busload of children, 34 children,\Nand they blow it up, kill all 34 children.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.16,0:30:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you explain such a thing?\NSo, Freud says that's the thanatos in the unconscious and they just invent the religion
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.38,0:30:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to give it a freedom of expression.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.47,0:31:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see it in the teenage killers.\NIn the United States, periodically, some teenage gets a gun and goes into his school
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.81,0:31:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,room and shoots all his classmates.\NAnd then he commits suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.14,0:31:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how can you explain it?\NYou can't explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.88,0:31:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWith intelligence or logic or rationality, you can only explain it with Freud's theory of Thanatos.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.08,0:31:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no other explanation.\NThis cannot be explained by intelligence or logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.99,0:32:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be explained by Freud's idea of Thanatos, which is attracted to death.\NIt can only be explained by that instinct, which is attracted to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.51,0:32:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have some time.\NIf so, I would like to know if there is a daily method that ordinary people can use to grow up with this dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.75,0:33:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams, just from intuitive, you can trust your intuition to look at your intuition to what this could be referring to.\NSo the dream might say to you, really, to look at this area, look at this area of your life and see what are your various motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.44,0:33:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Examine it, pay attention to it.\NSo the dream might serve a purpose that you pay attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.38,0:33:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So...\NIt's hard to do that, but if you make a suggestion, you can use your intuition to look at your dream and see what part of your life you want to observe in your dream, so you can dream and use your intuition to observe the things that you are missing in your life, as an opportunity to observe them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.65,0:33:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With, I guess, spiritual progression, what I'm thinking of is do the spiritual progression.\NAnyway, with spiritual progression, eventually...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.30,0:33:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get more and more enlightened, you hit a point where the dreams stop.\NI never dream anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.83,0:34:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I never dream anymore.\NIt might be because you don't need to repress anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.09,0:34:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, could be so.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.51,0:34:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NThe teachings that we hear from you, could they be used to help us to move beyond the level 700?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.61,0:34:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As work as a karma, they could help us go beyond the level 700.\NYou don't have to worry about going...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.17,0:34:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.\NYou don't have to worry about going to level 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.88,0:35:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You start the spiritual process, and then it goes where it goes.\NAnd you don't try and control.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.55,0:35:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no particular goal.\NThe person overall says, I want to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.03,0:35:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo that's a certain orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.69,0:35:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And wherever you are in the process is okay.\NIf you start spiritual work, don't try to control it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.88,0:35:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NWherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.19,0:35:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NWherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.92,0:35:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the state comes on spontaneously.\NThat state of consciousness occurs spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.86,0:36:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important is that...\NThe important thing is to be oriented in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.25,0:36:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As a life goal to become enlightened appeals to 1 in 10 million people on the street.\NThe desire to become enlightened, making that your prime goal in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.28,0:37:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,only 1 in 10 million people on the street, 1 in 10 million has that orientation.\NThat's one reason it's rare. It's few people choose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.94,0:37:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said,\NFortunate is to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.86,0:37:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,More fortunate than that is to be born a human and then to hear of enlightenment, to hear of it.\NRarer still is to hear of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.92,0:38:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then pursue it.\NSo we give thanks for the Buddha, for the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.40,0:38:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when we worship the Buddha, we pick up that energy that drives you through to the state of enlightenment.\NThat's why we revere the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.67,0:38:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ taught salvation. The Buddha taught enlightenment.\NJesus Christ taught salvation. The Buddha taught enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.30,0:38:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ taught salvation. The Buddha taught enlightenment.\NThis is a different question.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.76,0:38:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,10 years ago, the dark side of the inner world began to be seen and it has become more and more severe.\NIt is very painful because of this. How should we deal with these parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.76,0:39:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,About 10, since about 10 years ago, some dark spots within me, some dark side inside was spotted.\NDark side was what?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.01,0:39:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Was witnessed, was noticed by me.\NOh, he noticed. He noticed the dark spot in himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.01,0:39:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The dark spot in himself.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.01,0:39:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's getting severe and severe. And I've been sort of agonizing about it.\NIt's getting worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.01,0:39:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's getting worse and worse.\NWhat does he mean? Evil? Hate? What does he mean by dark spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.01,0:39:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?\NWhat do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.01,0:39:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotions and thoughts below 200. He's experiencing those emotions.\NYeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.01,0:39:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wants to overcome.\NWhat? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.01,0:40:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you lead a spiritual life, to overcome them.\NBecause it takes years for them to rise up and you stop repressing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.98,0:40:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You start to accept them.\NFirst, you accept the things you don't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.78,0:40:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people.\NI hate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.78,0:40:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people.\NI want to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.61,0:40:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.61,0:40:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you want to kill people. So what?\NThey have to be the way I want them to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.03,0:40:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to control them, make them different.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.03,0:41:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, you say, I don't want to make them different.\NThey can be how they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.21,0:41:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you say, people can't help being what they are.\NAnd then you realize that people can't change their own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.88,0:41:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't change that easily.\NThat's what I admit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.88,0:41:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You take a religious maniac and he wants to blow up a busload of children.\NHe blows up a busload of children.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.51,0:41:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a religious evangelist who tries to blow up a busload of children.\NTheIC MADASSAH
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.86,0:42:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's suffering fromŌĆöhis mind has been indoctrinated to think that way.\NSo the perpetrator is at the same time the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.75,0:42:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the victim of that kind of thinking.\NHe doesn't have to savor growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.88,0:42:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He has knowledge for that.\NWhen you take it, can you stand up for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.88,0:42:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\NSo, Jesus Christ said, there's only one sin, ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.92,0:42:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we forgive people because they don't know any better.\NOut of that arises the Buddha's compassion for all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.82,0:43:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion for all human beings. Compassion for their limitation.\NFirst of all, acknowledge that you have those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.01,0:43:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an expression. Acknowledge it and be at ease.\NOr do you just need to look at the negative emotions as they pass by?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.03,0:44:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch them subside without acting them out.\NHe can forgive himself for thinking those thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.05,0:44:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to forgive himself.\NSee, when you start looking at the unconscious, you have to accept what comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.13,0:44:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What comes up is usually...\N...not so pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.13,0:44:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you wouldn't have repressed it into your unconscious.\NWhen you check your consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.42,0:44:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,first, acknowledge the negative emotions that come up.\NBecause if they weren't so negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.42,0:44:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't have been suppressed unconsciously.\NSo, when you raise your consciousness to those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.42,0:45:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,even if they're negative, it's important to acknowledge them at ease.\NWhen you find the way to your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.28,0:45:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with the help of your teacher,\Nyou are studying to meet the true self through the inner conversation with the God of the nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.28,0:45:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you give me some advice?\NCan you explain about the consciousness of the nature before the Creator?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.71,0:45:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By seeking the way through heart,\Nshe met a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.86,0:45:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By seeking what?\NThe way through heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.86,0:45:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The way through the heart?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.86,0:45:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The way through love, yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.86,0:45:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, he met a teacher who taught her that to meet your true self,\Nyou have to have inner conversation with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.23,0:46:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She's doing that.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.86,0:46:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there good advice?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.86,0:46:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One more question.\NThis teacher is talking about some original consciousness prior to the Creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.50,0:46:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this possible?\NSome original consciousness prior?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.13,0:46:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to Creator.\NPrior to the Creator?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.13,0:46:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, prior to the Creator.\NMakes no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.76,0:46:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand. How?\NYou mean thoughts created God?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.17,0:46:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the question?\NYes, but he's giving explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.17,0:46:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Her teacher is giving explanations about some original consciousness prior to the Creator.\NOh, oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.30,0:46:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's doubting it.\NWhether that is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.44,0:46:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMy understanding of it is the same as pretty much revealed in Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.17,0:47:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning was the Godhead.\NThe beginning was the Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.40,0:47:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Godhead.\NOut of which arose God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.67,0:47:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which arose creation.\NThe first emanation from God was light, is symbolized as light.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.32,0:47:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the Godhead arose consciousness as light.\NOut of the light of God arose consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.63,0:48:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of consciousness arose the universe.\NThat is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.46,0:48:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.\NThat is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.46,0:48:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the consciousness arose the universe.\NAnd the universe was created to be evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.28,0:48:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's evolutionary by nature.\NThe universe was created to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.96,0:48:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was created to evolve in its essence.\NSo evolution is continuous and ongoing and eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.44,0:49:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why evolution is continuous and eternal.\NIt is measured by facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.30,0:49:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NDo you have any advice that she's seeking to meet her true self through inner conversations
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.30,0:49:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with God?\NThat's one style.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.30,0:49:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat's one style.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.13,0:49:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat's one style.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.13,0:49:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like divinity seeking to recognize its own divinity.\NIt's a paradox.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.71,0:49:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Like divinity seeking to recognize its own divinity.\NIt's a paradox that she brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.21,0:49:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That it was brought up.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.21,0:49:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.21,0:49:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.13,0:49:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.13,0:49:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.42,0:49:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.42,0:49:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.48,0:49:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.48,0:49:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.48,0:49:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.19,0:49:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.19,0:50:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.19,0:50:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.88,0:50:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.55,0:50:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.55,0:50:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.55,0:50:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.55,0:50:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.55,0:50:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.55,0:50:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.78,0:50:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHe's a dentist. He's been a dentist practicing for 10 years, and his observation is that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.86,0:50:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,people have bad habits like clenching your teeth and those things. These bad habits exert\Ncertain forces through your oral muscles, and then his guess is that leads to all the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.42,0:51:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,oral problems. He wants to know whether, through kinesiology, he wants to know whether that\Nis correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.50,0:51:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not sure about the question. People form nervous habits.\NYeah, by clenching their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.78,0:51:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I suppose clenching teeth is a way to diverge.\NBut anger, irritation, and he may be correct that by doing that, they do eventually pay
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.80,0:51:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain price. Yes, I think it's true.\NClenching their teeth all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.28,0:51:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.38,0:51:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If his observation is correct, he wants to know, confirm that through kinesiology.\NYeah, so he could say, confirm what?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.59,0:51:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether those bad habits leads to oral problems.\NOral diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.09,0:51:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NIt does, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.09,0:52:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.09,0:52:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And another question. He's doing Course in Miracle all by himself, without teacher.\NIs there any sort of dangers that he should be aware of?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.61,0:52:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dangers?\NYeah, doing alone, doing it all by himself, without teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.61,0:52:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, it's fine.\NAny danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.61,0:52:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat's one thing you can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.76,0:52:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah, it's not dangerous to forgive people.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.76,0:52:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For sure.\NAnd I forgot one more question for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.76,0:52:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHe then, he told his patients, stop doing that bad habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.09,0:52:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And patients do not listen to him.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.09,0:52:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wants to know how, how can he make his patients stop those bad habits more effectively.\NSometimes they do it without even, it's in their subconscious, because they don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.09,0:52:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,how to do it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.09,0:52:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.09,0:52:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.09,0:52:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.09,0:52:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.09,0:52:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.09,0:52:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.09,0:52:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.09,0:52:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.09,0:52:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.09,0:53:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHe tells them no, because they do some clutching the teeth is sometimes done
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.09,0:53:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in the sleep form, and you do it subconsciously rather than even consciously.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.78,0:53:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to retrain the patient, and use hypnosis perhaps.\NOh, and because there are a lot of cases of doing something goatie just like that has
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.34,0:53:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,been difficult, you need to re-educate the patient, to examinez the patient, and do some\Nwill help you a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.26,0:53:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep cleansing during the day, right?\NThat's almost all you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.50,0:53:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do that almost all day.\NYou have to fix it after you recognize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.80,0:53:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like hypnosis.\NBad habits are good for your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.84,0:53:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you.\NThat is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.00,0:54:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.01,0:54:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the true state of knowingness the same as the state of absolute love?\NAre those two the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.42,0:54:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NTwo different states.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.90,0:54:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NTwo different styles of trying to describe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.94,0:55:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the same.\NOh, knowingness on the level that he's asking this is very much the field in which this love occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.48,0:55:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Agape.\NThat type of love is called agape.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.48,0:55:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an impersonal way of being in the world, you know?\NThe two are the same, and they are two different ways of expressing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.34,0:55:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The state of the question you are asking is the same.\NThat is, the two levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.78,0:55:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The condition is that the level of love you get from this type of love, which is called agape.\NSo you're talking about love as the quality of your personality in terms of your personality in this world and What character are you speaking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.61,0:55:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI'm talking about all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.05,0:55:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,’┐Į\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.15,0:56:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Some unconscious patterns of bad behavior is repeating.\NAnd it happens so fast, like an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.76,0:56:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In an instant, it happens.\NSo it feels like an irremovable mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.38,0:56:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I overcome this?\NYou can.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.84,0:56:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're conquered.\NYou fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.42,0:56:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Collapse.\NGive up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.48,0:57:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Plead with God.\NAsk God.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.17,0:57:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of behavior?\NI think this is exactly what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.92,0:57:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of behavior are you talking about?\NFor example, in a couple's relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.90,0:57:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when they fight, they keep fighting in the same pattern.\NThey keep fighting with the same problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.01,0:57:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a complaint about my wife's insecurity.\NMy wife has a complaint about my lack of self-esteem and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.96,0:57:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a complaint about that.\NSo even if we keep fighting with different topics,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.17,0:57:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the focus keeps repeating.\NFor example, the fight, I mean, they have a fight with his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.42,0:58:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He fights, but over the same thing.\NShe complains about the fact that he's not generous enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.32,0:58:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd he's not satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.19,0:58:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That she is always sort of agitated.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.96,0:58:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And whatever the subject is, it ends up always with the same complaint.\NSo this pattern is repeating.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.88,0:58:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But it, yeah, that's his way.\NWell, stay that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.63,0:58:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to change.\NArgue.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.11,0:58:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Be unhappy.\NLay on the floor and cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.86,0:58:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit the floor.\NShe's crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.71,0:58:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NShe's crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.98,0:58:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.90,0:58:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Cry, cry, cry.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.25,0:59:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let her cry.\NAnd because this way she's trying to change him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.23,0:59:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the way she's trying to get her way in the world.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.09,0:59:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the baby.\NThe baby cries and cries.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.09,0:59:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And makes things happen.\NShe better grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.98,0:59:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And accept how the world is.\NYou have to stop being eight years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.63,0:59:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop being eight years old.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.03,0:59:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Grow up.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.76,1:00:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that isn't even tough.\NThat's just a minor problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.23,1:00:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what tough is.\NI mean, it doesn't create agony or, you know, something severe.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.01,1:00:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you're always blubbering and crying instead of, you know, cutting the potatoes\Nfor dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.19,1:00:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You get tears in the potatoes.\NYou get tears in the potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.48,1:00:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She has to give up.\NYou know, see, within each one, there is the adult, the child, and the parent.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.90,1:00:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a good pattern.\NWithin everybody, there is the child, the adolescent, the adult, and the parent.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.03,1:01:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,These sort of archetypes are in everybody's personality, and you give too much energy\Nto the child, you give too much energy to the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.86,1:01:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In you is also the parent.\NSo you say to the parent in you,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.90,1:01:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In you is also the parent.\NSo you say to the parent in you,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.05,1:01:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the child to stop that and grow up.\NTell the child to stop that and grow up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.09,1:02:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there is greater happiness, greater happiness to be found when you let go of being childish.\NBecause there is greater happiness, greater happiness to be found when you let go of being childish.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.80,1:02:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You then experience the happiness of the adult.\NAnd so indulging the child within you, you cheat your adult of the satisfaction of being
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.21,1:02:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a well-functioning, respectable adult, you see?\NSo by indulging the child in her, she's cheating the adult in her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.71,1:03:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to ask herself how she can help him be a better person, to make herself happy.\NSo is she saying he's stingy?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.96,1:03:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHe's stingy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.50,1:03:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not generous and kind enough.\NOh, emotionally.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.17,1:03:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionally, not money-wise.\NOh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.61,1:03:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And she needs to know that's how he is and accept that.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.65,1:04:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he will feel free to share his emotions with her.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.28,1:04:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another story.\NThere's another style of therapy called psychodrama.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.88,1:04:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychodrama.\NPsychodrama.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.07,1:04:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It might also be helpful.\NWhat does he think about what she says?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.63,1:04:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he think?\NYeah, he's not saying anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.42,1:04:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not saying anything.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.88,1:04:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She is always sort of emotionally agitated.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.23,1:04:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And fretting about things.\NOh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.78,1:04:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So what she needs to do is go off to where the emotion is.\NTo where she cries and gets all the emotions out.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.23,1:04:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then come back and talk with him.\NDon't cry in front of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.23,1:04:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, you know, no emotions in front of him.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.73,1:04:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she can sit down and talk with him after she's got all that emotion out of her.\NAnd he will respond better.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.80,1:05:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're emotionally agitated and anxious,\Ngo somewhere else and cry.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.32,1:05:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after you calm down,\Nit would be much better if you told your husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.61,1:05:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay.\NHe's smiling. He smiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.19,1:05:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He smiles.\NHe smiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.55,1:05:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's smiling at me.\NIs he, you know, is he happy with this relationship?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.55,1:05:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Or...\NAre you happy with this relationship?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.94,1:05:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy.\NThey feel happy about their relationship, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.96,1:05:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lie.\NThey are, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.96,1:05:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he smiles.\NHe's smiling.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.96,1:05:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He smiles.\NSo, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.96,1:05:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut she has a lot of emotions, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.96,1:05:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it could be from the baby.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.96,1:05:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually one reason,\Nthere is one reason for her emotional agitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.96,1:05:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She feels that I'm not a good person.\NShe feels I'm not a good person.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.96,1:05:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd she wants to...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.32,1:06:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So what she needs to do is channel that energy\Ninto becoming a good person
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.32,1:06:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so that she feels happy with herself, too.\NIt's hard to know what she means by good person.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.76,1:06:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.76,1:06:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She probably feels upset that she's got him upset.\NSo it was...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.76,1:06:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a ball that keeps rolling.\NVery low self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.76,1:06:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, yeah.\NShe has very low self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.76,1:06:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.76,1:06:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.84,1:06:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So that if she can help him be a good person,\NI think that would...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.17,1:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIf she channeled her energies into that,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.17,1:06:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be best.\NThen she takes all the emphasis off herself
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.17,1:06:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and onto him.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.17,1:06:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be better.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.32,1:06:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, more questions?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.32,1:06:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.76,1:06:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.76,1:06:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.34,1:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NThere's another couple.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.98,1:07:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Another couple, okay.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.26,1:07:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a question.\NJust...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.21,1:07:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here.\NCan you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.21,1:07:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NWhat's the question?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.07,1:07:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hear.\NI don't have a special question.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.05,1:07:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you don't have a question.\NBecause I'm here today...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.05,1:07:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,last year, I was a cancer patient,\Nand I was here to, you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.05,1:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went through the operation and chemotherapy.\NAnd while I was going through the process, I met your teaching.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.30,1:07:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And today I'm here just to express how grateful we are to have your presence in this life.\NAnd how grateful we are to have your teaching in this life.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.65,1:07:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.15,1:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So let us express our gratitude with the Korean traditional style of the bowing.\NWould you allow us to have the Korean way?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.07,1:08:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Korean way of bowing.\NThey want to express their gratitude through the Korean way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.82,1:08:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Korean way.\NWould that be okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.82,1:08:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, how do you do?\NOh, you just sit here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.34,1:08:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, you just sit.\NIt's new.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.50,1:08:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.\NSo you just sit and we will have a bow.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.10,1:08:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, I know what you mean.\NNow it's the divinity within.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.80,1:08:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, now it's the divinity within.\NI hear the voice inside me when I ask God a question during meditation or prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.22,1:09:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If I keep talking, the person asking the question disappears, the voice answering disappears, and there are often times when there is an answer that I want.\NThis is a desirable method.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.60,1:09:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true that the root of the sound that responds comes from God?\NWhile I'm meditating and praying and ask a question to God, I hear a voice within.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.82,1:09:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Within me, I hear a voice.\NAnd if I continue the conversation, then the person asking disappears and the person, the entity answering the question also disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.10,1:09:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer.\Nseeking exists just as as an answer with no entities talking is this a desirable
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.00,1:10:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,way it's useful useful and is the voice coming from God I don't know it depends\Non what you call God because God is all that is yes everything is coming from
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.19,1:10:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,God is it like a special transmission is it like is it like a special transmission\Nfrom God was this yes so it is the expression of God because it's a
